WEBVTT



00:00:00.960 --> 00:00:08.352
Welcome to the podcast for Perdido Bay Methodist Church. My name is Dudley. Today's February the ninth, Monday.

00:00:08.576 --> 00:00:14.112
Our reading is Matthew 12, verses 22 through 37.

00:00:14.048 --> 00:00:16.224
And in this reading,

00:00:16.224 --> 00:00:22.656
The Pharisees hear the crowd speaking of Jesus in messianic terms.

00:00:22.592 --> 00:00:26.112
So they attempt to discredit his ministry.

00:00:26.976 --> 00:00:28.928
They accuse him.

00:00:29.152 --> 00:00:32.000
Of casting out demons

00:00:31.680 --> 00:00:33.376
with the power

00:00:33.248 --> 00:00:35.008
Of the devil

00:00:35.712 --> 00:00:39.680
And in return Jesus accuses them of committing

00:00:39.424 --> 00:00:41.664
An unpardonable sin.

00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:46.976
He uses the illustration about a divided house to show that.

00:00:46.752 --> 00:00:48.352
It's unlikely.

00:00:48.192 --> 00:00:57.696
That someone is going to try to take themselves out of their own house, or someone is going to use negative power.

00:00:57.216 --> 00:00:59.776
To bring positive

00:00:59.616 --> 00:01:01.056
Results.

00:01:02.336 --> 00:01:04.672
Their argument makes no sense.

00:01:04.512 --> 00:01:06.880
Jesus states that if Satan,

00:01:06.944 --> 00:01:09.824
Was facilitating exorcisms?

00:01:09.728 --> 00:01:12.896
He would be counteracting his own attempts.

00:01:13.056 --> 00:01:14.656
To control the world.

00:01:15.456 --> 00:01:19.488
The religious leaders just would not believe.

00:01:19.200 --> 00:01:20.608
that Jesus

00:01:20.768 --> 00:01:21.920
Was good.

00:01:22.432 --> 00:01:26.656
It seems they were blinded by their own jealousies or their own ambitions.

00:01:27.456 --> 00:01:30.560
For all the good that Jesus had done, they felt that...

00:01:30.464 --> 00:01:35.392
His motives were deceptive, so they began to align him.

00:01:35.136 --> 00:01:40.160
With the side of the devil, the side of darkness, which is.

00:01:40.192 --> 00:01:41.504
Ludicrous.

00:01:43.008 --> 00:01:46.944
This reading concludes with an interesting statement from Jesus.

00:01:46.912 --> 00:01:53.248
2 and 35, it says, the good person out of his good treasure brings forth good.

00:01:53.312 --> 00:01:56.832
And the evil person out of his evil treasure.

00:01:56.768 --> 00:01:58.464
Brings forth.

00:01:58.560 --> 00:01:59.552
Evil.

00:01:59.808 --> 00:02:01.056
I tell you.

00:02:00.832 --> 00:02:07.456
On the day of judgment, people will give an account for every careless word they speak, for by your words.

00:02:07.232 --> 00:02:09.184
You will be justified.

00:02:09.312 --> 00:02:11.744
And by your words you will be condemned

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:13.696
By your words.

00:02:14.432 --> 00:02:15.744
This means

00:02:16.032 --> 00:02:19.456
Since words express the heart

00:02:19.456 --> 00:02:22.272
Good words demonstrate a good heart.

00:02:22.272 --> 00:02:23.968
And bad words.

00:02:23.712 --> 00:02:26.048
Demonstrate a bad heart.

00:02:26.528 --> 00:02:33.152
On the day of judgment, words will provide evidence for the nature and the position.

00:02:32.992 --> 00:02:34.688
Of the heart

00:02:35.744 --> 00:02:42.016
For this reason, it's important to allow God to continue to work in our hearts.

00:02:41.728 --> 00:02:46.016
To continue to shape us and mold us and form us.

00:02:46.304 --> 00:02:50.112
You see, the heart is like the CEO of ourselves.

00:02:49.856 --> 00:02:54.176
It's the place where our inner life choices are made and we

00:02:53.888 --> 00:02:56.736
Can be transformed by God.

00:02:56.736 --> 00:02:59.904
All the way down into our hearts.

00:02:59.712 --> 00:03:04.384
The heart is the place where our inner life choices are made.

00:03:04.416 --> 00:03:07.072
And it needs to be transformed.

00:03:07.392 --> 00:03:10.400
And we can be transformed by God.

00:03:10.400 --> 00:03:15.904
Let me encourage you to continue to make yourself available through actions

00:03:15.616 --> 00:03:18.976
That make transformation possible.

00:03:19.296 --> 00:03:20.384
prayer, prayer.

00:03:20.480 --> 00:03:22.112
Timing God's word.

00:03:22.432 --> 00:03:24.736
Christian community and worship.

00:03:24.736 --> 00:03:33.952
All of these are things that are life-changing, and through them, God will make sure that we are shaped into the person that we are.

00:03:33.824 --> 00:03:35.168
Who he

00:03:34.976 --> 00:03:36.544
wants us to be.

00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:42.304
And it's kind of funny that when we become the person that God wants us to be, we are perfect.

00:03:42.752 --> 00:03:44.032
Contempt.

00:03:43.872 --> 00:03:48.896
We are happy we are blessed in our own lives because we are functioning

00:03:48.832 --> 00:03:51.872
For the purposes that we were created.

00:03:52.224 --> 00:03:54.272
And this will make all the difference.

00:03:54.880 --> 00:03:58.240
God bless you as you continue your journey.

00:03:57.984 --> 00:03:59.360
With Jesus.

00:03:59.776 --> 00:04:01.280
Have a blessed day.
